# Pork Chops with Mushroom Gravy

> Seared pork chops served over egg noodles with a Campbells mushroom gravy and canned green beans. #pork #pasta #comfort

![](4A08536A-4BF2-4B1F-8029-8CB01F6AA0FB.jpeg)

Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

- Water |  | 
- Salt |  | 
- Egg Noodles |  | 

Bring seasoned water to a boil and cook noodles according to the package.

- Olive Oil |  | 
- Pork | Boneless Chop, 3 | 
- Salt |  | 
- Pepper |  | 

While water is heating up, heat oil over medium heat, season chops with salt and pepper on both sides and sear one side for 3 minutes, flip and cook in oven to an internal temperature of 165 degrees.

- Cream of Mushroom Soup | 1 can | 
- Milk | 1/2 cup | 

Cook soup and milk in a small pot over medium-low heat, whisking until smooth.

- Green Beans | 14 oz | 
- Butter | 1 tbsp | 
- Salt |  | 

Place green beans in a microwave safe container, top with butter, season with salt and heat in microwave for 1.5 minutes.
